<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Vibration Damper, Crankshaft,
        Main Bearings, Flywheel, and Crankcase - Remove - Remove Rear Wear Sleeve
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s210010702.6" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Remove Rear Wear Sleeve</title>
        <svcsubproc id="s210010702.6.2">
            <title>Rear Oil Seal Carrier Removed</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With rear oil seal carrier removed, tap outside diameter of wear sleeve.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>This will cause wear sleeve to expand and slide off easily.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove and discard wear sleeve.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s210010702.6.1">
            <title>Rear Oil Seal Carrier Installed</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To avoid possible damage to engine, do not nick crankshaft flange.</para>
                </caution>
                <note>
                    <para>This method may be used when repair is to be done in chassis with flywheel housing in place.
                    </para>
                </note>
                <note>
                    <para>The rear oil seal carrier should not be removed and replaced if there is no leakage or the
                        crankshaft is not being removed.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_206.xml" xrefid="t210010704">Rear Wear Sleeve Remover (ZTSE4404)</hotlnk>
                    guide plate against crankshaft . Assemble three collets around wear sleeve, guide plate and
                    crankshaft flange.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010717" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/eg5175.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Assemble Wear Sleeve Removal Tool</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble sleeve over three collets on crankshaft flange.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010718" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/eg5176.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Assemble sleeve</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Hold guide plate while turning forcing screw to remove wear sleeve. Remove wear sleeve
                    from sleeve remover. Discard wear sleeve.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010719" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/eg5177.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Remove wear sleeve</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect crankshaft flange for damage.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
